WEBVTT

00:06.966 --> 00:08.676
Previously on
The Summer I Turned Pretty...

00:08.759 --> 00:10.761
[Conrad] No matter what happens,
we'll still be infinite.

00:10.845 --> 00:13.723
[Belly] I wasn't in Cousins.
Conrad and I weren't together.

00:13.806 --> 00:14.849
And Susannah was dead.

00:14.932 --> 00:15.891
[Steven] You screwed up

00:15.975 --> 00:17.393
and now everything is weird

00:17.476 --> 00:19.228
- with Conrad and Jeremiah.
- I was in in love, Steven.

00:19.311 --> 00:20.730
What was I supposed to do?!

00:20.813 --> 00:22.106
Your guidance counselor
emailed me.

00:22.189 --> 00:24.525
I didn't know you lost
your volleyball captaincy or

00:24.608 --> 00:26.610
- that your grades were so bad.
- You were barely here.

00:26.694 --> 00:28.738
Belly? A-Are you with Conrad?

00:28.821 --> 00:31.657
He's not answering my texts
or picking up my calls.

00:31.741 --> 00:33.200
I think I'm gonna go
to Brown in the morning.

00:33.284 --> 00:34.577
Okay.

00:34.660 --> 00:36.537
But I'm coming with you.

00:39.582 --> 00:41.584
♪ ♪

00:52.136 --> 00:54.013
[phone chimes]

01:03.939 --> 01:05.941
[♪ One Direction:
"Steal My Girl"]

01:16.869 --> 01:18.871
♪ ♪

01:29.381 --> 01:31.884
♪ She's been my queen
since we were 16 ♪

01:31.967 --> 01:34.720
♪ We want the same things,
we dream the same dreams ♪

01:34.804 --> 01:39.140
♪ All right, all right ♪

01:41.477 --> 01:43.729
♪ I got it all
'cause she is the one...

01:43.813 --> 01:45.731
- Hi.
- Hey.

01:45.815 --> 01:47.858
I can't believe you're here.

01:47.942 --> 01:48.943
Yeah, me neither.

01:50.444 --> 01:53.614
♪ All right...

01:53.697 --> 01:54.824
You didn't bring a coat?

01:54.907 --> 01:58.369
Uh, I forgot, but I'm not cold.

02:00.371 --> 02:02.581
- Put this on.
- [giggles]

02:02.665 --> 02:04.250
[panting]

02:04.333 --> 02:06.460
♪ Everybody wanna
take her heart away ♪

02:06.544 --> 02:08.336
♪ Couple billion
in the whole wide world...

02:08.419 --> 02:10.923
- Want to go to the beach?
- Yeah!

02:11.006 --> 02:12.925
♪ 'Cause she belongs to me ♪

02:13.008 --> 02:14.969
♪ Na, na, na, na-na ♪

02:15.052 --> 02:17.805
♪ Oh, yeah, all right ♪

02:17.888 --> 02:20.683
♪ Na, na, na, na-na ♪

02:20.766 --> 02:23.811
♪ She belongs to me ♪

02:23.894 --> 02:25.437
♪ All right ♪

02:25.521 --> 02:28.566
♪ Na, na, na, na-na ♪

02:28.649 --> 02:31.318
♪ She belongs to me ♪♪

02:45.040 --> 02:46.333
[message sends]

02:52.923 --> 02:55.426
[Belly] Maybe I should
just tell her the truth.

02:55.509 --> 02:58.178
It was my mom who took Conrad
to the emergency room

02:58.262 --> 02:59.930
the time he broke his arm
skateboarding.

03:00.014 --> 03:02.808
Susannah was shaking so hard
she couldn't drive.

03:02.892 --> 03:06.061
My mom has always
been steady, solid.

03:06.145 --> 03:08.606
She always knows what to do.

03:08.689 --> 03:11.358
Or at least she used to.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.194
Now I'm not so sure.

03:18.324 --> 03:19.366
[message sends]

03:22.077 --> 03:23.287
[Jeremiah] Hey, Aubrey.

03:23.370 --> 03:24.997
Uh, yeah, I'm good.

03:25.079 --> 03:27.583
Hey, listen,
have you talked to Conrad

03:27.666 --> 03:30.461
at all lately or seen him?

03:31.795 --> 03:33.422
No? All right.

03:33.505 --> 03:34.798
All right, talk to you later.

03:34.882 --> 03:35.799
Hey, what up, McIntyre?

03:35.883 --> 03:38.093
Hey. By any chance, um,

03:38.177 --> 03:40.054
are you with
my brother right now?

03:41.889 --> 03:44.683
Oh, okay.
Uh, no, man, I'm sorry.

03:44.767 --> 03:46.936
I thought, I thought you guys
were still hanging out. My bad.

03:47.019 --> 03:48.395
Hey, Brian.

03:48.478 --> 03:51.398
Um, it's Jeremiah,
Conrad's brother.

03:51.482 --> 03:53.817
Um, hey, listen,
this is kind of a long shot,

03:53.901 --> 03:56.528
but have you
talked to him lately?

03:56.612 --> 03:58.113
[sighs]

03:58.197 --> 04:01.492
No? All right. Yeah.
Yeah, no worries.

04:05.496 --> 04:06.747
Fuck!

04:18.425 --> 04:20.427
[phone chimes]

04:28.686 --> 04:30.562
[groans, sniffs]

04:30.646 --> 04:31.981
You're up early.

04:32.064 --> 04:35.275
Well, yeah, no. I can never
sleep in when I drink.

04:35.359 --> 04:37.361
[Laurel] What was that?

04:37.444 --> 04:40.739
Um, well, I mean,
not that I ever really drink.

04:40.823 --> 04:41.907
[both chuckle]

04:41.991 --> 04:43.784
W-Where's Belly?

04:43.867 --> 04:45.494
I'm gonna, I'm gonna
wake her ass up, too.

04:45.577 --> 04:48.372
With Taylor. Apparently
she and Milo broke up.

04:48.455 --> 04:49.790
Oh.

04:49.873 --> 04:52.084
You can give her a call
if you need something.

04:52.167 --> 04:56.714
No, no, it's nothing.
I-I'll catch up with her later.

04:56.797 --> 04:59.591
Hey, so I'm going to go
to that bookseller's

04:59.675 --> 05:00.968
meet and greet in New York
tomorrow.

05:01.051 --> 05:02.386
What? Wait.
Good for you.

05:02.469 --> 05:03.929
You'll be okay on your own
for a couple nights?

05:04.013 --> 05:05.180
Or do you want to stay
with your dad?

05:05.264 --> 05:07.766
Mom, I'm going off to college.

05:07.850 --> 05:09.643
- I'll be fine.
- Okay.

05:09.727 --> 05:12.896
Then let me at least
feed you breakfast.

05:12.980 --> 05:15.983
Mm, no, I'm good.
[chuckles]

05:16.066 --> 05:17.568
We have no food.

05:17.651 --> 05:19.361
It was Belly's turn
to go to the store.

05:19.445 --> 05:21.405
I can make you eggs.
Nice and runny.

05:21.488 --> 05:22.781
Great for a hangover.

05:22.865 --> 05:26.285
Mm. No. No, thank you.

05:26.368 --> 05:28.162
Let's just go get
something to eat, yeah?

05:28.245 --> 05:30.247
Come on.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.207
- [chuckles]
- All right.

05:32.291 --> 05:34.293
♪ ♪

05:39.214 --> 05:42.259
[indistinct chatter]

05:42.342 --> 05:44.595
[line ringing]

05:44.678 --> 05:46.597
[phone buzzing]

05:46.680 --> 05:48.057
Hey.

05:48.140 --> 05:49.266
[Belly] Hey, um, I'm here.

05:49.349 --> 05:50.476
Where?

05:50.558 --> 05:53.353
Uh, on campus somewhere.

05:53.437 --> 05:54.772
- Are you not...?
- I am.

05:54.855 --> 05:56.356
I'm heading to
Conrad's dorm now.

05:56.440 --> 05:57.524
All right? Meet me there.

05:57.608 --> 05:59.234
- [line beeping]
- Uh...

05:59.318 --> 06:02.863
♪ Will I start to feel
like I'm whole? ♪

06:02.946 --> 06:04.698
[indistinct chatter]

06:04.782 --> 06:06.658
Hey, Jeremiah.

06:06.742 --> 06:08.410
Belly, hey.

06:08.494 --> 06:09.870
I got you this.

06:09.953 --> 06:12.247
Um, I'm good. Thanks.

06:12.331 --> 06:14.458
Thanks for coming all this way.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.001
[Belly] Have you heard
anything from Conrad?

06:16.085 --> 06:17.211
[Jeremiah] Nothing.

06:17.294 --> 06:19.880
He hasn't answered my calls
or my texts.

06:21.173 --> 06:22.925
It's a good thing you're here
though, because I don't know

06:23.008 --> 06:24.593
what floor he's on
or what room he's in.

06:24.676 --> 06:25.969
I don't either.

06:26.053 --> 06:28.222
I mean, I know he's on
the top floor, but that's it.

06:28.305 --> 06:30.724
You never visited him at Brown?

06:30.808 --> 06:32.643
Yeah, my mom wasn't thrilled

06:32.726 --> 06:34.520
about the idea of me driving
four and a half hours

06:34.603 --> 06:36.730
to go see, you know, my, uh...

06:36.814 --> 06:38.690
[door opens]

06:38.774 --> 06:40.400
[Belly clears throat]

06:48.784 --> 06:51.662
[both sigh]

06:51.745 --> 06:53.956
This is it.

06:54.039 --> 06:55.832
Yeah.

06:58.335 --> 06:59.837
Hello?

07:03.507 --> 07:05.717
[Belly] Hey, look,
his bed is made.

07:05.801 --> 07:08.595
I mean, things can't be so dire
if his bed is made, right?

07:08.679 --> 07:11.932
Whoa. Excuse me.
This is my room

07:12.015 --> 07:13.517
that you guys
are rifling through.

07:13.600 --> 07:17.312
Hey, man. I'm Conrad's brother.
We talked on the phone earlier.

07:17.396 --> 07:19.648
- It's nice to finally meet you.
- Okay. Jeremiah, right?

07:19.731 --> 07:21.275
- Yeah.
- Cool.

07:21.358 --> 07:22.776
Um, hey, Connie's not back,
is he?

07:22.860 --> 07:26.488
Uh, I haven't seen him
since Thursday afternoon.

07:26.572 --> 07:28.115
Did anything else
happen before he left?

07:28.198 --> 07:30.325
He got into it with
somebody on the phone.

07:30.409 --> 07:32.619
Like, he was yelling and shit.

07:32.703 --> 07:34.163
And then he just took off?
Do you have any idea

07:34.246 --> 07:35.372
who he was yelling at?

07:35.455 --> 07:36.832
I don't know, bro.
The government

07:36.915 --> 07:39.001
who's surveilling us through
our devices as we speak.

07:40.961 --> 07:43.463
Is that the last time
you heard from him?

07:43.547 --> 07:45.549
No. He texted me this morning
saying that he was

07:45.632 --> 07:48.093
gonna miss bio lab
and asked if I could take notes.

07:48.177 --> 07:50.929
I'd be annoyed,
but I spent this whole year

07:51.013 --> 07:53.348
copying off of his shit,
so I can't really complain.

07:53.432 --> 07:54.641
Y'all feel? [chuckles]

07:54.725 --> 07:58.228
Mm. Would you mind just,
like, trying to call him

07:58.312 --> 07:59.980
from your phone and seeing
if he answers?

08:00.063 --> 08:01.148
Yeah, for sure.

08:01.231 --> 08:03.358
Trusky, did I leave
my sweater in here?

08:03.442 --> 08:05.027
- [Trusky] Uh, I don't...
- [line ringing]

08:05.110 --> 08:07.196
One sec. I don't know.
Maybe...

08:07.279 --> 08:08.405
[Conrad] Hey, it's Conrad.
Leave a message.

08:08.488 --> 08:09.531
No.

08:09.615 --> 08:11.575
Straight to voice mail.

08:11.658 --> 08:13.869
But Sophie might know
where Conrad went.

08:13.952 --> 08:15.370
- They're tight.
- Hey.

08:17.206 --> 08:20.834
Hey, Sophie, um, you wouldn't
happen to have any idea where

08:20.918 --> 08:22.377
- my brother disappeared to?
- Um...

08:22.461 --> 08:23.879
I think he said
he was going to hang out

08:23.962 --> 08:26.632
with his cousin by the beach.

08:26.715 --> 08:28.884
All right, Belly, let's go.

08:28.967 --> 08:32.429
Oh, yeah, you're Belly.
Yo...

08:32.511 --> 08:35.557
when you guys broke up,
my man fell into a depression.

08:35.640 --> 08:38.684
Uh, I-I don't think
that was because of me.

08:38.769 --> 08:41.395
No, yeah, it definitely was.

08:41.480 --> 08:44.107
Like, he was always looking
at your picture on his phone.

08:45.901 --> 08:48.320
Anyways, when you guys find him,
tell him that he has to

08:48.403 --> 08:50.739
be back for this bio final
on Thursday

08:50.822 --> 08:52.074
or he doesn't pass the class.

08:52.157 --> 08:53.992
- Wait, seriously?
- [Trusky] Yeah.

08:54.076 --> 08:55.702
Okay. Um, I'll grab
his computer.

08:55.786 --> 08:58.038
You grab his books
and stuff so he can study. Okay?

08:59.081 --> 09:00.457
Come on.

09:00.540 --> 09:03.001
♪ ♪

09:03.085 --> 09:05.087
[Jeremiah] Are these Conrad's?

09:05.170 --> 09:06.880
So I can just take all these?

09:06.964 --> 09:09.299
[Trusky] Yeah, all that stuff
is his. You can take it.

09:09.383 --> 09:10.926
[Jeremiah] Let's go, Belly.

09:13.220 --> 09:14.304
[Trusky] Good luck.

09:14.388 --> 09:15.514
Thanks.

09:16.640 --> 09:18.642
[vehicle chirps]

09:18.725 --> 09:22.396
Um, the next bus leaves
in half an hour, so...

09:22.479 --> 09:24.773
Why would he take off
like that to Cousins?

09:24.856 --> 09:27.359
I don't think he's missed
a day of class in his life.

09:27.442 --> 09:28.902
Not even when Mom was sick.

09:28.986 --> 09:30.779
I'm not sure.

09:30.862 --> 09:33.448
Who was he yelling at
on the phone?

09:33.532 --> 09:36.243
I mean, it had to have
been Dad, right?

09:36.326 --> 09:38.453
What could they
possibly be arguing about?

09:38.537 --> 09:40.622
Yeah, no, no, it was probably
Adam. I mean, he and Conrad

09:40.706 --> 09:42.082
are always disagreeing
on something.

09:43.834 --> 09:45.877
I really don't want to get
dragged in the middle

09:45.961 --> 09:47.754
of whatever bullshit
Conrad's in right now,

09:47.838 --> 09:50.841
but if something were to
happen to him, I wouldn't be

09:50.924 --> 09:52.509
- able to forgive myself.
- Hey. No, no, no.

09:52.592 --> 09:56.138
Nothing has happened
to Conrad, okay?

09:57.306 --> 09:59.182
I mean, I'm sure he's
just spending the day surfing

09:59.266 --> 10:01.435
and he has his phone off.

10:01.518 --> 10:02.769
Maybe.

10:04.062 --> 10:05.731
But it's only been
a month since...

10:10.402 --> 10:12.571
You know how he is.
He just bottles up all that shit

10:12.654 --> 10:13.989
until at some point it explodes.

10:14.072 --> 10:16.658
I don't think he has anyone.

10:16.742 --> 10:18.493
He definitely
hasn't been talking to me.

10:18.577 --> 10:22.748
All right. Do you want me
to come with you to Cousins?

10:22.831 --> 10:25.000
I didn't need you to come here.

10:26.626 --> 10:29.004
I think I can handle things
fine on my own.

10:29.087 --> 10:31.673
No, I know you can.
But you don't have to.

10:31.757 --> 10:33.216
I mean, if you
need me to come...

10:33.300 --> 10:35.677
I don't.

10:38.096 --> 10:42.225
Maybe Conrad does. He still
cares what you think about him.

10:46.063 --> 10:48.732
[Belly] I know that
even though he won't say it,

10:48.815 --> 10:52.444
Jeremiah wants me to come
because he's afraid.

10:52.527 --> 10:55.822
I still know this boy better
than I know almost anyone.

10:55.906 --> 10:58.784
- So I'll go for him.
- [engine starts]

10:58.867 --> 11:01.703
Um, I'm coming with you.

11:02.746 --> 11:03.747
[Laurel] Since we're
at the mall, I guess

11:03.830 --> 11:04.748
I should get something to wear

11:04.831 --> 11:06.833
- for this book thing.
- Mm-hmm.

11:06.917 --> 11:08.877
Want to come clothes shopping
with me?

11:08.960 --> 11:10.295
[chuckles] Yeah, no offense,

11:10.379 --> 11:11.755
but that kind of sounds
like my worst nightmare.

11:11.838 --> 11:13.507
[chuckles] Fine.

11:14.674 --> 11:17.177
Oh... Mm-mm.

11:17.260 --> 11:18.428
Breakfast is my treat.

11:18.512 --> 11:19.471
That's very sweet,

11:19.554 --> 11:21.098
but save your money
for textbooks.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.557
No, I've got that
covered already.

11:22.641 --> 11:24.810
My Cultural Celebration
scholarship money

11:24.893 --> 11:26.603
came through.
And, if I get the one

11:26.686 --> 11:29.022
that Big Dairy sponsors,
my meal plan money's set, too.

11:29.106 --> 11:30.941
You applied
for a dairy scholarship?

11:31.024 --> 11:33.610
Oh, yeah. No, I, like,
totally gamed the system.

11:33.693 --> 11:34.861
I built an entire database

11:34.945 --> 11:36.696
and then categorized
and cross-referenced

11:36.780 --> 11:39.116
by type of essay.
I thought I told you.

11:40.492 --> 11:42.411
Yeah, no, you did.

11:46.957 --> 11:49.000
Do you know your sister
got a D in trig?

11:49.084 --> 11:50.877
She was doing okay at
the beginning of the year,

11:50.961 --> 11:54.089
and then she just
dropped the ball.

11:54.172 --> 11:55.590
Well, Belly's grades have
always been mediocre.

11:55.674 --> 11:56.925
We've known this.

11:57.008 --> 11:58.969
But she was always
a solid B student, not D's.

11:59.052 --> 12:01.763
Well, not everyone
can be a Princeton man.

12:01.847 --> 12:03.265
[both chuckle]

12:03.348 --> 12:05.809
Can you please
try talking to her?

12:05.892 --> 12:09.479
Yeah, I'm not sure she wants
to hear from me right now.

12:09.563 --> 12:11.398
We got into a fight
at the party last night.

12:11.481 --> 12:13.483
I feel kind of bad.

12:13.567 --> 12:16.903
Yeah? We got into it
last night, too.

12:16.987 --> 12:18.363
Mm?

12:18.447 --> 12:20.031
According to her,
I'm a neglectful mother

12:20.115 --> 12:21.741
and everything wrong
in her life is my fault.

12:21.825 --> 12:22.951
[Steven scoffs]

12:23.034 --> 12:24.286
And I know Taylor got dumped,

12:24.369 --> 12:26.496
but I'm sure she's also
staying over there to punish me.

12:26.580 --> 12:27.956
Yeah, probably the both of us.

12:28.039 --> 12:29.749
Do you think I'm a bad mom?

12:31.084 --> 12:33.336
I can cancel this thing in
New York if you guys need me...

12:33.420 --> 12:34.838
Mom, stop trying
to get out of it.

12:34.921 --> 12:37.424
You should go
and promote your book.

12:37.507 --> 12:40.802
Let's just give Belly
some space, okay?

12:40.886 --> 12:43.096
And I will keep an eye
on her on my end.

12:45.140 --> 12:46.725
You really are grown up.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.729
Yeah, yeah, I am the best.

12:50.812 --> 12:52.939
Now, go try on
some boring pantsuit, okay?

12:53.023 --> 12:54.441
I'm gonna hit the B&N.

12:54.524 --> 12:56.026
Okay.

13:07.454 --> 13:08.914
- [♪ Sofia Mills:
"Coffee Breath"]
- ♪ Woke up in ♪

13:08.997 --> 13:10.624
♪ Your new apartment in your...

13:10.707 --> 13:11.791
[Jeremiah clears throat]

13:11.875 --> 13:13.335
Did, uh... Were you about...

13:13.418 --> 13:14.920
Were you gonna say something?

13:15.003 --> 13:16.713
Nope.

13:17.964 --> 13:19.382
Okay.

13:19.466 --> 13:21.384
♪ All I know is that
you talk too much ...

13:21.468 --> 13:25.805
- [ringtone playing]
- [Belly clears throat]

13:25.889 --> 13:27.474
[phone clicks, ringtone stops]

13:27.557 --> 13:29.518
Was that Steven?

13:29.601 --> 13:30.644
Why didn't you pick up?

13:30.727 --> 13:32.896
I'll call him later.

13:34.314 --> 13:36.733
♪ You've got those
big blue eyes ♪

13:36.816 --> 13:38.527
♪ Drive me crazy...

13:38.610 --> 13:41.905
Hey, how, uh...
how have you been?

13:41.988 --> 13:43.782
- Since...
- I'm okay.

13:43.865 --> 13:46.117
Because you know I'm here.

13:46.201 --> 13:48.870
If you ever need to talk.

13:48.954 --> 13:51.039
♪ Call me Dahmer 'cause ♪

13:51.122 --> 13:53.583
♪ Your heart's so tasty ♪

13:53.667 --> 13:55.335
♪ Ba-ba-dum ♪

13:55.418 --> 13:59.214
♪ Ba-ba-dum-badumba ♪

13:59.297 --> 14:00.966
♪ Da-ba-dum ♪

14:01.049 --> 14:02.968
♪ Ba-ba-dum...

14:03.051 --> 14:04.386
You know, I...

14:04.469 --> 14:07.514
went to Cousins with
my mom for the spring once.

14:07.597 --> 14:09.933
♪ Said it's my mistake...

14:10.016 --> 14:12.978
It's kind of weird being there
when it's not summer.

14:13.061 --> 14:15.188
♪ So I tried my best...

14:15.272 --> 14:17.649
Yeah, I bet.

14:17.732 --> 14:19.818
♪ I've been...

14:19.901 --> 14:21.570
[Conrad] On a scale of
one to ten, how much trouble

14:21.653 --> 14:24.072
do you think we'll be in when
they find out we're gone?

14:24.155 --> 14:26.116
Oh, I'm not getting
into any trouble.

14:26.199 --> 14:27.951
I'm telling everyone
you kidnapped me.

14:28.034 --> 14:29.160
What? Please.

14:29.244 --> 14:30.996
You jumped at the chance.

14:31.079 --> 14:34.583
Yeah, only because
I've never seen a snowy beach.

14:34.665 --> 14:36.209
Me either.

14:36.293 --> 14:38.211
Last time I checked
the weather out, there was only

14:38.295 --> 14:42.132
a 30% chance of flurries,
but hopefully we'll get lucky.

14:42.215 --> 14:44.801
Hey, did Susannah like the bike
you got her for Christmas?

14:44.884 --> 14:46.386
You got the one
with the basket, right?

14:46.469 --> 14:48.555
- Yeah. Yeah, she loved it.
- Yeah.

14:48.638 --> 14:51.516
Thanks to you. I was just
gonna get her a bathrobe.

14:51.600 --> 14:54.644
I know, that is what
Steven got my mom this year.

14:54.728 --> 14:56.730
- Really?
- Yeah.

14:56.813 --> 14:58.607
Why do boys suck so bad
at giving presents?

14:58.690 --> 15:03.528
Honestly... I don't think she
would have cared what I got her.

15:04.821 --> 15:08.533
You have no idea how happy she
is that you're my girlfriend.

15:11.244 --> 15:13.204
Hey, I haven't told anyone yet,
but I think I'm gonna

15:13.288 --> 15:15.832
switch my major to biology.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.751
- Really? Wow.
- Yeah. I want to go premed.

15:17.834 --> 15:19.419
- Wow.
- And for a while,

15:19.502 --> 15:21.004
I thought I wanted to go
into the research end of it,

15:21.087 --> 15:24.799
but no, I think I'd rather
be working with actual people.

15:26.051 --> 15:27.177
Because of your mom?

15:29.262 --> 15:31.973
She's getting better, you know.

15:33.642 --> 15:36.144
♪ ♪

15:36.227 --> 15:38.271
Will you try, uh, Conrad again?

15:39.314 --> 15:41.191
[smacks lips] Yeah.

15:42.317 --> 15:44.944
[line ringing]

15:49.908 --> 15:51.534
No answer.

15:54.162 --> 15:56.331
We actually haven't talked
since the funeral.

15:57.415 --> 15:58.792
What the hell
happened with you guys?

16:01.294 --> 16:03.213
He never said anything?

16:07.842 --> 16:09.636
We don't talk about you.

16:09.719 --> 16:11.179
[tire pops]

16:11.262 --> 16:12.681
- [air hissing]
- Oh, shit.

16:12.764 --> 16:14.099
[Jeremiah exhales]

16:16.017 --> 16:17.060
[both sigh]

16:17.143 --> 16:19.562
Great. Great.

16:19.646 --> 16:21.189
Great.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.776
Thank you. Thank you.

16:27.737 --> 16:29.739
♪ ♪

16:31.866 --> 16:34.536
[chuckles] What are you doing
at a bookstore?

16:34.619 --> 16:36.162
I'm just grabbing Starbucks.

16:36.246 --> 16:37.747
Where's, uh, where's my sister?

16:37.831 --> 16:39.749
Isn't she
supposed to be with you?

16:39.833 --> 16:42.460
Uh, yeah, she is. She's just...
[stammering]

16:42.544 --> 16:44.421
She's just grabbing
Auntie Anne's.

16:44.504 --> 16:47.924
Oh. I-I'm sorry, by the way.

16:48.007 --> 16:49.426
About what?

16:50.719 --> 16:54.389
About you and Milo breaking up.

16:54.472 --> 16:56.975
[sighs heavily]
Yeah, I'm really...

16:59.018 --> 17:02.188
[mock cries]
...pretty devastated, you know.

17:03.857 --> 17:07.068
Okay, not to be,
like, a dick or anything,

17:07.152 --> 17:09.612
but you seem less
devastated than I expected.

17:09.695 --> 17:11.531
I mean, considering you
were practically swallowing

17:11.614 --> 17:13.199
- his tongue last night.
- Leave it to you

17:13.282 --> 17:14.742
to make kissing
sound disgusting.

17:14.826 --> 17:17.078
No, no, no, no,
the two of you kissing is.

17:17.162 --> 17:19.580
No, no, "was."

17:20.999 --> 17:23.917
- I-I'm sorry.
- [sighs]

17:24.002 --> 17:26.838
Anyways, you could...

17:26.921 --> 17:28.506
do better.

17:28.590 --> 17:30.175
Milo is the best guy
I've ever dated.

17:30.258 --> 17:31.301
Oh.

17:31.384 --> 17:34.345
I mean... I mean, he was.
[sighs]

17:34.429 --> 17:35.930
I'm just...
Yeah, I don't know.

17:36.014 --> 17:38.475
Like, maybe we'll
get back together.

17:38.558 --> 17:39.809
Great.

17:39.893 --> 17:42.771
Yeah, awesome.
No, I mean, he's just so...

17:42.854 --> 17:45.398
great, you know?

17:46.524 --> 17:48.485
Um...

17:48.568 --> 17:50.320
Isn't my sister waiting
for you or...?

17:50.403 --> 17:52.113
- Yeah.
- Actually, I kind of,

17:52.197 --> 17:53.198
I kind of need to talk to her

17:53.281 --> 17:54.657
- for a sec if you...
- No. Steven,

17:54.741 --> 17:56.534
she is still mad at you
about the party, okay?

17:56.618 --> 17:58.787
And if you talk to her now,
you'll spin her out.

17:58.870 --> 18:00.246
Right now I'm the one
who gets to spin out.

18:00.330 --> 18:02.248
Yeah, because of the breakup.
So, ciao.

18:02.332 --> 18:03.583
Uh...

18:21.351 --> 18:23.603
♪ ♪

18:27.816 --> 18:29.400
Shopping for a special occasion?

18:29.484 --> 18:30.860
Just a work thing.

18:30.944 --> 18:32.779
So something conservative, then?

18:32.862 --> 18:34.697
I'm a writer
and I have a new book out,

18:34.781 --> 18:35.990
but I have to promote
in New York.

18:36.074 --> 18:39.661
I'm a huge reader.
What's your name?

18:41.246 --> 18:42.539
Laurel Park.

18:44.082 --> 18:45.667
You wrote Party's Over.

18:47.001 --> 18:48.795
My divorcée book club
read it last summer.

18:48.878 --> 18:51.548
[chuckles]
So, what's your new book about?

18:51.631 --> 18:54.509
It's a memoir about
me and my best friend.

18:54.592 --> 18:55.760
What's it called?

18:55.844 --> 18:58.221
It's called
It's Not Summer Without You.

18:59.681 --> 19:02.141
- Can I try this on?
- Of course.

19:02.225 --> 19:04.477
And I'll grab you
a few more options, too.

19:04.561 --> 19:06.271
Thank you.

19:06.354 --> 19:08.273
[bird cawing]

19:10.400 --> 19:13.486
[ringtone playing]

19:15.405 --> 19:18.199
My God, Steven
will not leave me alone.

19:19.659 --> 19:21.202
Who are you calling?

19:21.286 --> 19:26.082
AAA, because in case you didn't
realize, the tire's done for.

19:26.165 --> 19:28.001
Well, we can just
change it ourselves.

19:28.084 --> 19:29.669
It's not that hard.

19:29.752 --> 19:33.006
My mom taught me
before I took my driver's test.

19:33.089 --> 19:35.592
Can we just leave it
to the experts, please?

19:35.675 --> 19:37.886
Uh, I am an expert.

19:37.969 --> 19:40.555
All we got to do
is take the jack out

19:40.638 --> 19:42.932
and then take
the spare off the back.

19:43.016 --> 19:45.310
That's... that is not
for decoration?

19:45.393 --> 19:47.729
No.

19:47.812 --> 19:50.398
Okay, yeah, sure.
Let's do it.

19:54.277 --> 19:56.905
- You need help?
- Nope. This it?

19:56.988 --> 19:58.448
Yeah. Okay.
You got to put that

19:58.531 --> 20:00.533
behind the wheel
so the car doesn't move.

20:00.617 --> 20:03.077
- Okay. Like here?
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

20:04.704 --> 20:06.164
Good?

20:06.247 --> 20:08.291
- Um, yeah, is that right?
- Okay. Yep.

20:08.374 --> 20:09.876
Now we have to lift the car.

20:09.959 --> 20:11.711
- Lift the car?
- Lift the car.

20:11.794 --> 20:13.546
- Okay.
- Okay.

20:13.630 --> 20:14.923
- [Belly] You got it.
- It's not as straightforward

20:15.006 --> 20:16.299
as you're making it sound.

20:16.382 --> 20:17.508
- It's working...
- Don't lift it too high, okay?

20:17.592 --> 20:18.885
[Jeremiah] I'm not
lifting it too high.

20:18.968 --> 20:20.970
Move a little bit closer
to the wheel.

20:21.054 --> 20:22.764
- What? I...
- Move closer to
the wheel, okay?

20:22.847 --> 20:25.266
- Just a little bit closer.
- I can't. You need me
to move...

20:25.350 --> 20:27.268
You need to move
closer to the wheel.

20:27.352 --> 20:28.728
I feel like it can't get
any more self-explan...

20:28.811 --> 20:30.438
Shit! Fuck!

20:32.440 --> 20:34.192
Great idea with this, Belly.

20:34.275 --> 20:36.277
- It's not my fault.
- [scoffs]

20:36.361 --> 20:37.695
Seriously?

20:37.779 --> 20:39.238
This was your fucking idea.

20:39.322 --> 20:40.823
Now I'm covered in dirt.

20:40.907 --> 20:42.825
It's 100 degrees outside. And
if you would have just let me

20:42.909 --> 20:44.285
call AAA,
they'd probably be here already.

20:44.369 --> 20:46.871
I'm sorry! Okay?

20:46.955 --> 20:50.500
Thanks. So helpful.

20:50.583 --> 20:52.168
No, Jere, not about this, okay?

20:52.251 --> 20:55.838
I'm sorry. I'm really
sorry about everything.

20:55.922 --> 20:58.758
About what happened
at the funeral.

20:58.841 --> 21:00.718
You think I'm pissed
about the funeral?

21:02.136 --> 21:03.429
The funeral was fucked.

21:03.513 --> 21:05.098
Everyone was messed up.

21:05.181 --> 21:06.599
I'm pissed about last summer.

21:08.810 --> 21:10.353
Belly, you were my best friend.

21:10.436 --> 21:12.897
We hooked up, and then
you hooked up with my brother.

21:12.981 --> 21:14.232
And then everyone
expected me to act

21:14.315 --> 21:16.234
like I was fine, and I wasn't!

21:16.317 --> 21:18.820
Okay, well, the last thing
that we wanted, that...

21:18.903 --> 21:21.447
that I wanted, was to hurt you.

21:21.531 --> 21:22.448
And that's why Conrad
and I didn't

21:22.532 --> 21:23.825
get together
at the end of the summer.

21:23.908 --> 21:26.411
Yeah, Belly, for what?
All of five minutes?

21:26.494 --> 21:28.496
That was just so you guys
wouldn't look bad.

21:28.579 --> 21:30.832
I mean, you were seeing other
people. We thought you were

21:30.915 --> 21:32.166
- over it.
- Because otherwise, I was that

21:32.250 --> 21:34.377
pathetic loser that was
keeping you guys apart.

21:34.460 --> 21:36.879
[scoffs] I'm sorry.

21:38.256 --> 21:39.632
Sorry for what?

21:39.716 --> 21:41.884
For Conrad dumping you?

21:41.968 --> 21:43.928
Did you really not
see that coming, Belly?

21:44.012 --> 21:45.430
Because I sure did.

21:46.472 --> 21:49.350
[scoffs]
I'm sorry because I miss you.

21:49.434 --> 21:50.893
[scoffs]

21:50.977 --> 21:53.688
I've missed you for months.

21:53.771 --> 21:55.898
That's why
I called you last night.

21:55.982 --> 21:58.317
Yeah, because
Conrad wasn't picking up.

21:58.401 --> 22:01.446
Jere, you are the one
I called, not him.

22:07.785 --> 22:10.038
Look, when Susannah was sick,
I was...

22:10.121 --> 22:12.206
[exhales]

22:12.290 --> 22:17.003
I was so focused on Conrad
and on being there for him,

22:17.086 --> 22:19.589
and I should have been
there for you, too, okay?

22:20.631 --> 22:23.760
And I forgot about you.
And I hate myself for that. I...

22:29.098 --> 22:31.142
Jere...

22:33.644 --> 22:36.397
- I hate that I let you down.
- [sniffles]

22:40.193 --> 22:41.903
It happened so fast.

22:41.986 --> 22:43.863
Belly, it was really,
really bad.

22:44.864 --> 22:47.075
I had Dad and Conrad sort of,

22:47.158 --> 22:51.079
but I needed you,
and you just weren't there.

22:51.162 --> 22:53.164
[crying] You left me.

22:56.709 --> 22:58.169
Hey.

23:00.922 --> 23:03.091
I'm here now.

23:03.174 --> 23:04.675
I'm not going anywhere.

23:06.969 --> 23:08.221
Yeah.

23:08.304 --> 23:10.431
♪ ♪

23:13.017 --> 23:14.310
Can I see?

23:16.604 --> 23:18.106
Uh...

23:18.189 --> 23:19.315
It's fine.

23:19.398 --> 23:21.025
But it's not good enough
for an event in New York

23:21.109 --> 23:22.652
with a bunch
of other famous writers.

23:22.735 --> 23:25.029
[chuckles] I'm about as unfamous
as a writer can be.

23:25.113 --> 23:28.116
[laughs] You can't be unfamous
if I've heard of you.

23:28.199 --> 23:29.408
[chuckles]

23:31.410 --> 23:33.079
Try this on.

23:33.162 --> 23:34.705
It's got the wow factor.

23:34.789 --> 23:35.957
[laughs]

23:36.040 --> 23:37.834
That sounds like
something Beck would say.

23:37.917 --> 23:39.877
- Who's Beck?
- Uh, she's my...

23:39.961 --> 23:41.087
Um...

23:41.170 --> 23:43.506
She was my best friend.

23:44.674 --> 23:46.425
- I didn't...
- You know what?

23:46.509 --> 23:48.219
I think I will try this on.

23:48.302 --> 23:49.637
Oh. [chuckles softly]

23:50.930 --> 23:52.265
[exhales]

23:54.433 --> 23:56.435
[shuddering]

24:00.606 --> 24:02.608
[Steven sighs]

24:12.160 --> 24:13.494
[creaking]

24:13.578 --> 24:15.621
I need to talk to my sister.
Now.

24:15.705 --> 24:18.541
She's not here right now.

24:18.624 --> 24:20.960
She just went to the store.
For Twix.

24:21.043 --> 24:23.171
So, earlier,
she was getting Auntie Anne's

24:23.254 --> 24:24.172
and now she's getting Twix?

24:24.255 --> 24:26.674
And? We're on our periods.

24:26.757 --> 24:28.634
- Get over it, you baby.
- [scoffing] Okay.

24:28.718 --> 24:30.303
So then why did she send me
a text earlier saying

24:30.386 --> 24:32.180
you guys
were cry-watching Titanic

24:32.263 --> 24:35.308
at the very same moment
I saw you at the mall?

24:35.391 --> 24:36.392
Hmm?

24:37.393 --> 24:40.104
- [stammers] Because...
- [stammers] "Becau-Because..."

24:40.188 --> 24:42.190
- [stammering]
- [groans] Fine.

24:43.274 --> 24:45.484
I'll tell you. We just...

24:45.568 --> 24:46.736
You can't freak out.

24:46.819 --> 24:48.070
Yeah. Okay. Yeah.

24:48.154 --> 24:49.822
She's with Jeremiah.

24:49.906 --> 24:51.949
Conrad was MIA,
but they figured out that he's

24:52.033 --> 24:53.868
in Cousins, so they're on their
way to go get him right now.

24:53.951 --> 24:56.245
Wait, wait, wait.
But they're not even talking.

24:56.329 --> 24:58.623
Why-why would Jere call her
and not me?

24:58.706 --> 24:59.832
I don't know.
Maybe 'cause you're such

24:59.916 --> 25:00.875
a pain in the ass all the time.

25:00.958 --> 25:01.959
No. Okay,
I need to talk to Jere.

25:02.043 --> 25:03.419
Wait. No, no.
Please wait. No, no, no.

25:03.502 --> 25:05.546
Can you please just let Belly
handle this by herself?

25:05.630 --> 25:07.340
Please?

25:07.423 --> 25:08.382
She feels so shitty
about how things are

25:08.466 --> 25:09.383
with the boys right now.

25:09.467 --> 25:11.135
Like, she knows she screwed up.

25:11.219 --> 25:12.386
Yeah, she did.

25:12.470 --> 25:13.804
Yeah.

25:13.888 --> 25:15.973
And you made her
feel like crap about it.

25:17.266 --> 25:20.353
So, please, just let her
fix this by herself.

25:21.604 --> 25:23.439
Fine, fine, fine, fine.

25:23.522 --> 25:24.982
Okay? I'll let her try
and clean up her mess.

25:25.066 --> 25:27.318
But you need to tell me
anything you hear, okay?

25:27.401 --> 25:29.362
[scoffs] Okay.

25:30.404 --> 25:31.405
[sighs]

25:31.489 --> 25:32.823
Okay, stalker.

25:32.907 --> 25:34.200
Like, bye.

25:34.283 --> 25:36.369
[♪ Del Water Gap:
"Ode to a Conversation..."]

25:39.080 --> 25:41.999
♪ I do not want to fight this...

25:42.083 --> 25:45.336
[stomach gurgling]

25:45.419 --> 25:47.088
Oh, my God,
was that your stomach?

25:47.171 --> 25:49.131
Shut up. I'm starving.

25:49.215 --> 25:51.050
All I had to eat today
was an Icee.

25:51.133 --> 25:52.677
And even I know
that doesn't count as a meal.

25:52.760 --> 25:54.637
Well, lucky for you,

25:54.720 --> 25:56.055
we are almost to pie.

25:56.138 --> 25:57.932
Rosie's?

25:58.015 --> 25:59.976
So you want to stop or...

26:00.059 --> 26:02.144
Ow.

26:02.228 --> 26:03.646
Yes.

26:03.729 --> 26:05.273
[chuckles]

26:05.356 --> 26:08.192
♪ And it hits me ♪

26:08.276 --> 26:12.363
♪ I don't want anybody else
touching you like I do ♪

26:12.446 --> 26:13.572
♪ Like I do ♪

26:13.656 --> 26:16.367
♪ Like me ♪

26:16.450 --> 26:18.995
♪ Is it okay? ♪

26:19.078 --> 26:23.040
♪ That I don't want anybody else
touching you like I do ♪♪

26:23.124 --> 26:26.836
[indistinct chatter]

26:30.506 --> 26:31.590
[exhales]

26:31.674 --> 26:33.592
Okay. Um...

26:33.676 --> 26:35.845
I think I'm gonna get...

26:35.928 --> 26:37.096
- Blueberry?
- ...blueberry.

26:37.179 --> 26:38.264
Yeah? Weird.

26:38.347 --> 26:39.932
Yeah. You always
could read my mind.

26:40.016 --> 26:41.392
Mostly. I mean...

26:41.475 --> 26:43.227
I'm glad it's back anyway,
our ESP.

26:43.311 --> 26:45.104
- Yeah, me, too. [sniffs] Okay.
- Mm.

26:45.187 --> 26:46.856
- Oh.
- I know that you're not eating

26:46.939 --> 26:49.400
any pie because...
[inhales sharply]

26:49.483 --> 26:51.527
mm, you're worried
about ruining your abs.

26:51.610 --> 26:53.070
- [gasps]
- Yeah.

26:53.154 --> 26:55.364
[scoffs] I mean,
they are a service to mankind,

26:55.448 --> 26:56.532
- so...
- Mm.

26:56.615 --> 26:58.034
Maybe not. Maybe.
You never know.

26:58.117 --> 27:00.411
- Mm.
- Belly?

27:00.494 --> 27:02.413
- Nicole!
- [gasps, laughing]

27:02.496 --> 27:03.664
- Hi!
- Hi!

27:03.748 --> 27:05.166
Oh...

27:05.249 --> 27:06.459
[chuckles]

27:06.542 --> 27:08.961
Jere, I was so sorry
to hear about your mom.

27:09.045 --> 27:10.588
She was so lovely.

27:11.589 --> 27:13.174
Yeah. She was.

27:13.257 --> 27:14.675
Thank you.

27:14.759 --> 27:17.762
Hey, I think, uh,
our order's ready.

27:17.845 --> 27:20.097
- Yeah. Yeah. Uh, me, too.
- If you want to go grab it.

27:22.725 --> 27:24.143
How are he and Conrad doing?

27:24.226 --> 27:26.771
I reached out after the funeral,
but I never heard back,

27:26.854 --> 27:28.439
and I figured
things were intense, so...

27:28.522 --> 27:30.858
Yeah, you know, they're hanging
in there. [chuckles softly]

27:30.941 --> 27:32.109
Um, how-how have you been?

27:32.193 --> 27:34.278
Have you seen any
of the-the debs yet this summer?

27:34.362 --> 27:36.655
Uh, I saw Marisa last week,
but, uh,

27:36.739 --> 27:39.825
Gigi's dad got caught
in some insider trading thing

27:39.909 --> 27:41.035
and they had
to sell their house.

27:41.118 --> 27:43.662
- Oh, wow.
- Yeah. Really awful.

27:43.746 --> 27:45.873
And supposedly they're making
a documentary about it.

27:45.956 --> 27:49.460
And Shayla's in Europe
with her parents all summer.

27:49.543 --> 27:50.836
And so the gang's broken up.

27:50.920 --> 27:52.463
But I guess that was bound
to happen at some point.

27:52.546 --> 27:54.048
Yeah. That's so... It's too bad.

27:54.131 --> 27:55.216
Yeah.

27:55.299 --> 27:56.509
What about you?
I didn't even know

27:56.592 --> 27:58.052
you guys were coming this year.

27:58.135 --> 27:59.887
Yeah, we weren't. It, um...

27:59.970 --> 28:01.555
It just... It kind of came up.

28:01.639 --> 28:03.516
Well, we should definitely hang.

28:03.599 --> 28:05.267
- You still have my number?
- Mm-hmm.

28:05.351 --> 28:07.228
- Awesome. All right, bye.
- Bye.

28:07.311 --> 28:09.605
♪ ♪

28:11.107 --> 28:13.692
[Belly] We both know
I won't call.

28:13.776 --> 28:16.195
It doesn't feel the same
as last summer.

28:16.278 --> 28:17.863
- [♪ Olivia Rodrigo: "deja vu"]
- ♪ Car rides ♪

28:17.947 --> 28:20.574
♪ To Malibu ♪

